Date: 0/0/1993
Source: Politics, Economics & Pastoral Land
Author: ACKROYD
Vol / Page: 11
Edition:
Quote: A pastoral licensee could use his, and rarely her, pre-emptive rights to lock up the land along a mile of road for the cost of the fencing, say GBP60, when to buy the same land outright would cost a settler GBP600 .. in some cases huts and fences would be erected to obtain a pre-emptive right over the adjacent land after which they were pulled down and put up elsewhere to enable fresh claims to be made.
